<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457742>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Bayesian phylogenetic relationships based on mtDNA (COI and 16S) of the genus Lampromeloe Reitter, 1911. High bayesian posterior probabilities (> 98%) are denoted by a dot on each corresponding node." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457742/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457744>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Dorsal view of the pronotum. A–D. Lampromeloe variegatus (Donovan, 1793). E–H. L. cavensis (Petagna, 1819). I–J. L. pantherinus sp. nov. A. Tardáguila, Salamanca (Spain). B. Palencia de Negrilla, Salamanca (Spain). C. Fuente el Sauz, Ávila (Spain). D. Naharros de Valdeunciel, Salamanca (Spain). E. Ben Slimane (Morocco). F–G. Essaouira, Moulay Bouzerktoun (Morocco). H. Linares, Jaén (Spain). I. Holotype, ♂ (MNCN_Ent 325513) from Tizi n’Tichka (Morocco). J. Paratype, ♂ (MNCN_Ent 325515) from El Hajeb, Fès-Meknès region (Morocco). Photographs by AS-V." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457744/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457746>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Lateral view of the elytra. A–C. Lampromeloe variegatus (Donovan, 1793). D–F. L. cavensis (Petagna, 1819). G–H. L. pantherinus sp. nov. A. Vértesszőlős (Hungary). B. Topas, Salamanca (Spain). C. Fuente el Sauz, Ávila (Spain). D. Mohamedia (Morocco). E. Linares, Jaén (Spain). F. Ben Slimane (Morocco). G. Holotype, ♂ (MNCN_Ent 325513) from Tizi n’Tichka (Morocco). H. Paratype, ♂ (MNCN_Ent 325515) from El Hajeb (Morocco). Photographs by AS-V." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457746/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457748>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Male genitalia, from left to right: dorsal and lateral view of the tegmen, and lateral view of the aedeagus. A. Lampromeloe pantherinus sp. nov., holotype (MNCN_Ent 325513). B. L. variegatus (Donovan, 1793) from Salamanca, Palencia de Negrilla (MNCN_Ent 375546). Photographs by AS-V. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457748/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457750>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Upper central: selected landmarks (red dots) in the pronotum (dorsal side) used in this study. Upper sides: deformation grids showing extremes of shape variation represented by L. cavensis (Petagna, 1819) (left) and L. variegatus (Donovan, 1793) (right). Below: Principal Component Analysis of pronotum shape among the three species of Lampromeloe Reitter, 1911. Empty red dots represent specimens of L. pantherinus sp. nov., empty blue dots L. variegatus, and empty green dots L. cavensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457750/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457752>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. Lampromeloe pantherinus sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (MNCN_Ent 325515) from El Hajeb, Morocco. A. Dorsal view. B. Frontal view. Photographs by AS-V." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457752/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457754>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Meloe stellata Pliginskij, 1923, syntype (MNB). Photograph by AS-V." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457754/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457756>
    dc:description "Fig. 9. Distribution of Lampromeloe pantherinus sp. nov. Known records and type locality are depicted by red dots and a white star, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457756/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457758>
    dc:description "Fig. 10. Surroundings of Tizi n’Tichka, Morocco. Type locality of Lampromeloe pantherinus sp. nov. Photograph by MG-P." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457758/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10457760>
    dc:description "Fig. 11. Habitus of Moroccan living specimens of Lampromeloe. A–C. L. pantherinus sp. nov. D. L. cavensis (Petagna, 1819). A–B. Holotype, ♂ (MNCN_Ent 325513) and paratype, ♂ (MNCN_Ent 325514) from Tizi n’Tichka. C. Paratype (ECWP 24078) from Jbel Tsiwant. D. Sidi Ifni. Photographs by MG-P (A–B), A. François (C), and AS-V (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10457760/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

